# AssetProof — local environment configuration
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values.
# .env.local is never committed to source control.

# ── Proof publishing ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# PROOF_PUBLISHER_NETWORK controls which publish path is used.
# Omit or leave blank to use dry-run mode (no chain config required).
#
# Supported values:
#   relay        — POST the proof payload to PROOF_PUBLISHER_ENDPOINT.
#                  The relay handles chain submission (BSC testnet or mainnet).
#   bsc-testnet  — Legacy alias for relay, accepted for backward compatibility.
#   bas-direct   — BAS SDK slot (placeholder, not yet active).
#                  Falls back to relay if PROOF_PUBLISHER_ENDPOINT is set,
#                  otherwise equivalent to dry-run.
#
# PROOF_PUBLISHER_NETWORK=relay
# PROOF_PUBLISHER_ENDPOINT=https://your-relay.example.com/attest
# PROOF_PUBLISHER_API_KEY=

# ── BAS direct (placeholder — not yet active) ────────────────────────────────
#
# When BAS SDK integration ships, these will configure the direct path.
# Leave blank until the bas-direct mode is implemented.
#
# BAS_SCHEMA_UID=0x...
# BAS_GRAPHQL_ENDPOINT=https://bas.bnbchain.org/graphql
# BAS_RPC_ENDPOINT=https://bsc-dataseed.bnbchain.org
